---

<Layout
  title="Dry Lining Cost Guide 2026 | Edinburgh & Lothians Pricing & Service Guide"
  description="Comprehensive 2026 dry lining cost guide for Edinburgh and the Lothians. Residential & commercial pricing per m², timeframes, insurance requirements, payment terms, and how to avoid cowboy builders."
  canonical="/resources/dry-lining-cost-guide/"
>
  <main class="container" style="padding: 34px 0 70px;">

    <!-- Schema Markup -->
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(orgJsonLd)} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(articleJsonLd)} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(serviceJsonLd)} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqJsonLd)} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(breadcrumbJsonLd)} />

    <!-- Hero Image -->
    <section style="max-width: 860px; margin-bottom: 18px;">
      <div class="card" style="padding: 0; overflow: hidden;">
        <img
          src="/images/services/dry-lining.png"
          width="1200"
          height="630"
          alt="Professional dry lining work in an Edinburgh residential property showing plasterboard installation"
          loading="eager"
          fetchpriority="high"
          style="display:block; width:100%; height:auto;"
        />
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Article -->
    <article class="card" style="padding: 28px; max-width: 860px;">

      <!-- Hero Title -->
      <header style="margin-bottom: 22px;">
        <h1 style="margin:0 0 10px; font-size: clamp(26px, 4vw, 36px); line-height: 1.15;">
          Dry Lining Cost and Service Guide 2026
        </h1>
        <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 16px; margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">
          The most comprehensive pricing and service guide for dry lining, plastering, partitioning, and ceilings in Edinburgh, Leith, and the Lothians. Updated July 2026 with live trade data, regional cost indices, and verified contractor quotes.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- TL;DR -->
      <section style="background: rgba(196,30,58,0.05); border-left: 4px solid var(--primary); padding: 16px 18px; border-radius: 0 10px 10px 0; margin-bottom: 28px;">
        <h2 style="margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 18px;">TL;DR — Quick Reference</h2>
        <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 18px; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.7; font-size: 14px;">
          <li><strong>Residential dry lining:</strong> £26 – £47 per m² (walls); £29 – £50 per m² (ceilings)</li>
          <li><strong>Commercial dry lining:</strong> £23 – £42 per m² (economies of scale)</li>
          <li><strong>Metal stud partitioning:</strong> £52 – £95 per linear metre (single-layer)</li>
          <li><strong>Suspended ceilings:</strong> £31 – £57 per m² (flat designs)</li>
          <li><strong>Plastering:</strong> £21 – £37 per m² (skim coat); £29 – £47 per m² (full re-plaster)</li>
          <li><strong>Rendering:</strong> £42 – £68 per m² (sand &amp; cement); £85 – £128 per m² (silicone)</li>
          <li><strong>Edinburgh vs national:</strong> Slightly above UK average for labour</li>
          <li><strong>Single room:</strong> 1 – 2 days | <strong>Whole house:</strong> 1 – 2 weeks | <strong>Commercial fit-out:</strong> 2 – 4 weeks</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 1: Residential Costs -->
      <section style="margin-bottom: 28px;">
        <h2 id="residential-costs" style="font-size: 22px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Cost Per Square Metre — Residential</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--text-light); line-height: 1.65; margin-bottom: 14px;">
          Residential dry lining costs in Edinburgh and the Lothians vary by board type, finish level, and access. The figures below include materials and labour. Edinburgh sits slightly above the UK national average for plastering and dry lining labour day rates due to demand in the city.
        </p>
        <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
          <table style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 14px;">
            <thead>
              <tr style="background: rgba(245,251,249,0.9);">
                <th style="border:1px solid var(--border); padding:10px; text-align:left;">Type of Work</th>
                <th style="border:1px solid var(--border); padding:10px; text-align:left;">Typical Cost per m²</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {residentialCosts.map((row) => (
                <tr>
                  <td style="border:1px solid var(--border); padding:10px;">{row.service}</td>
                  <td style="border:1px solid var(--border); padding:10px; font-weight:650;">{row.cost}</td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6;">
          <strong>Note:</strong> A typical 3-bedroom house dry lining project in Edinburgh ranges from £3,700 to £8,000 depending on finish level, insulation requirements, and whether ceilings are included. Single rooms (small bedroom) typically cost £550 – £1,300.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 2: Commercial Costs -->
      <section style="margin-bottom: 28px;">
        <h2 id="commercial-costs" style="font-size: 22px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Cost Per Square Metre — Commercial</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--text-light); line-height: 1.65; margin-bottom: 14px;">
          Commercial dry lining benefits from economies of scale. Larger projects, repeat specifications, and open-plan spaces reduce per-m² costs. Fire-rated and acoustic specifications are more common in commercial work across Edinburgh's business districts and retail parks.
        </p>
        <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
          <table style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 14px;">
            <thead>
              <tr style="background: rgba(245,251,249,0.9);">
                <th style="border:1px solid var(--border); padding:10px; text-align:left;">Type of Work</th>
                <th style="border:1px solid var(--border); padding:10px; text-align:left;">Typical Cost per m²</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {commercialCosts.map((row) => (
                <tr>
                  <td style="border:1px solid var(--border); padding:10px;">{row.service}</td>
                  <td style="border:1px solid var(--border); padding:10px; font-weight:650;">{row.cost}</td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6;">
          <strong>Note:</strong> Commercial office fit-outs of 500 – 1,000 m² in Edinburgh typically range from £16,000 to £42,000 depending on partition complexity, ceiling type, and whether fire-stopping and acoustic treatment are required.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 3: Cost Breakdown by Service Type -->
      <section style="margin-bottom: 28px;">
        <h2 id="service-breakdown" style="font-size: 22px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Cost Breakdown by Service Type</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--text-light); line-height: 1.65; margin-bottom: 14px;">
